<subSubSection id="C32C6541FFB8045AEB8FACBA23D1FC54" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8936CAFFB8045AEB8FACBA23D1FC54" blockId="1.[151,1437,644,920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis id="B942EAD8FFB8045AEB8FACBA216CFD51" bold="true" box="[151,273,644,669]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C364D49FFB8045AEA02ACBA21FAFD51" authorityName=", Simon" authorityYear="1897" box="[282,391,644,669]" class="Arachnida" family="Philodromidae" genus="Psellonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAD8FFB8045AEA02ACBA21FAFD51" box="[282,391,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Psellonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D49FFB8045AE881ACBA2443FD51" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[921,1086,644,669]" class="Arachnida" family="Philodromidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Philodromidae</taxonomicName>
by the flat, frontally truncated prosoma (
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEA11AC992113FD0C" box="[265,366,679,704]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1410,241,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[179,1410,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Psellonus planus. Male. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D–F left pedipalp (D ventral, E retro-lateral, F pro-lateral). Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.1 mm, D–F 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: E—embolus; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; S—subtegulum; SP—sperm duct; T—tegulum; TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEA64AC9621DDFD0C" box="[380,416,680,704]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[183,1410,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[183,1410,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3A–E. Psellonus planus. Female. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D epigyne, ventral; E vulva, dorsal. Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.2 mm, D 0.1 mm, E 0.05 mm. Abbreviations: FD—fertilization duct; SPM—spermathecae; SPO—spermathecal organ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">3A</figureCitation>
) in combination with a unique eye configuration (both eye rows occupying full width of cephalothorax, MEQ strongly trapezoid, more than 3 times wider than long, AER straight, PER slightly recurved, AER much narrower than PER, PME smaller than other eyes (
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AE84CACD123A4FCC4" box="[852,985,751,776]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[183,1410,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[183,1410,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3A–E. Psellonus planus. Female. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D epigyne, ventral; E vulva, dorsal. Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.2 mm, D 0.1 mm, E 0.05 mm. Abbreviations: FD—fertilization duct; SPM—spermathecae; SPO—spermathecal organ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 3A, C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AE8FDACCE2475FCC4" box="[997,1032,752,776]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,193,1965]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1427,193,1966]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4A–H. Natural history of Psellonus planus. Photo credit: Mr. Jimmy Paul" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">4A</figureCitation>
) and strongly elongated mouthparts (labium more than 3 times longer than wide, endites elongated, convergent blades (
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEF4CAD2A24C4FCE0" box="[1108,1209,788,813]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1410,241,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[179,1410,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Psellonus planus. Male. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D–F left pedipalp (D ventral, E retro-lateral, F pro-lateral). Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.1 mm, D–F 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: E—embolus; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; S—subtegulum; SP—sperm duct; T—tegulum; TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEFDFAD2A2497FCE0" box="[1223,1258,788,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[183,1410,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[183,1410,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3A–E. Psellonus planus. Female. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D epigyne, ventral; E vulva, dorsal. Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.2 mm, D 0.1 mm, E 0.05 mm. Abbreviations: FD—fertilization duct; SPM—spermathecae; SPO—spermathecal organ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">3B</figureCitation>
). A similar eye configuration is found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D49FFB8045AEAAEAD0922B0FC9C" authority="Balogh" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1936" box="[438,717,823,848]" class="Arachnida" family="Philodromidae" genus="Pseudopsellonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAD8FFB8045AEAAEAD09220EFC9C" box="[438,627,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Pseudopsellonus</emphasis>
Balogh
</taxonomicName>
, but labium and endites are not elongated in this genus. Further diagnostic characters are seen in the chelicerae, which show strong bulges in both sexes (
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEF6CAD6224ABFCB8" box="[1140,1238,860,885]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1410,241,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[179,1410,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2A–F. Psellonus planus. Male. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D–F left pedipalp (D ventral, E retro-lateral, F pro-lateral). Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.1 mm, D–F 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: E—embolus; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; S—subtegulum; SP—sperm duct; T—tegulum; TA—tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AEFF9AD622578FCB8" box="[1249,1285,860,884]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[183,1410,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[183,1410,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3A–E. Psellonus planus. Female. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D epigyne, ventral; E vulva, dorsal. Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.2 mm, D 0.1 mm, E 0.05 mm. Abbreviations: FD—fertilization duct; SPM—spermathecae; SPO—spermathecal organ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">3C</figureCitation>
). In the male, however, the chelicerae are strongly divergent and modified (
<figureCitation id="130D2A4FFFB8045AE85EAD4123E3FC54" box="[838,926,895,920]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[183,1410,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[183,1410,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3A–E. Psellonus planus. Female. A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C chelicerae, dorsal; D epigyne, ventral; E vulva, dorsal. Scale bars: A 0.5 mm, A 0.5 mm, B 0.3 mm, C 0.2 mm, D 0.1 mm, E 0.05 mm. Abbreviations: FD—fertilization duct; SPM—spermathecae; SPO—spermathecal organ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
